works.description: The black Asprey bag which was a symbol of authority to the former Prime Minister of the United Kingdom, Margaret Thatcher, is all set to go under the hammer. The auction of the bag will be by Christie’s in June and is expected to fetch around £100,000. The iconic bag is special in many regards as it was carried by the lady whenever she used to head for important meetings like with US president Ronald Reagan and Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev.
